			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Have you ever watched the base of a pet and marked their position in the floor and then watch how often they keep creeping forward in order to keep in the melee box?  This is because they are pushing the mob.  Anyone that can melee, has the ability to push the mob through their melee, but pets ability to push mob can be as much as 20 times greater than any PC melee class.  Their ability to push mobs is so ridiculously over powered; it is to the point of being destructive to a raiding force.  When you take in account of multiple pet classes on a raid, their combined pets can cause many problems such as pushing mobs out of PC’s melee box, causing ping ponging.  They can push mobs to areas not reachable by PC players, if their masters are not playing attention and backing them off.  They can push an NPC that the main tank is on out of range from the healers, causing the main tank to die and there for causing the rest of the raid to crumble and fail.
<br />

<br />
This problem most noticeable in situations where the PoP mob has some type of area of effect, that the healers are trying to avoid and are healing from max spell casting range.  The slightest movement forward or backwards of the mob and the raid fails.
<br />

<br />
This has become such a problem with high level PoP raids, that for the most part, all pets have been banned on raids because of placement issues they cause from pushing the mobs.  If they could make pets not push mobs at all or very little, it would greatly improve beastlords DPS in the high level raiding game. 
<br />

<br />
P.S.  Also remove the pets /say spam messages when you tell you pet /pet back off or /pet hold or turn them into tells to the pet's master only.  Getting 12 lines of /pet hold /pet back off after each mob on a raid where pets are used, sucks so badly since it cannot be filtered.<br />_________________<br /><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450587>Maujin Buu</a>: 65 Feral Lord - Prexus
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450605>Gramz Thull</a>: 61 Warlord - Prexus (retired)
<br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450498>Feelx Junglevibe</a>: 61 Hierophant - Prexus (taxi)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
