			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The pet does NOT have more push than you do, although it will likely outpush a warrior swinging a slow 2HB. You and the pet together have twice the push of any other melee, so YOU can influence where the mob is going simply by placing yourself and the pet appropriately.
<br />

<br />
If you're having trouble with push, you're not positioning your pet correctly. I often place my pet on the same side as the tank (until it enrages anyway), to help counter the partys push. Sometimes I'll put myself there as well, if it's really important.
<br />

<br />
As for getting to nonaccessible areas, that's true...but it's not the pets fault, it's the fault of whoever had the aggro for not turning the mob before it was a problem.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
