<br />

<br />
This has become such a problem with high level PoP raids, that for the most part, all pets have been banned on raids because of placement issues they cause from pushing the mobs. If they could make pets not push mobs at all or very little, it would greatly improve beastlords DPS in the high level raiding game. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
What mobs are these you are talking about?
<br />

<br />
If all of your pet classes send the pets form the same spot, hell yes it is gonna screw up mob placement when you add 8 "people" pushing from the same spot - but that is a handler error.
<br />

<br />
You mentioned the key reason why pets are worthless in a lot of fights, but yet ignored it.  AE's. Yes the push can be tricky, but the reason I dont use mine is the AE or the AE rampage. The pet flat cant take it.  Mobs that AE flurry for 3k, or ae cast for 2k is gonna eat a pet up so fast, that healing them is a waste of time. At that point, buffing the stew out of them & spending 1/2 of the fight trying to keep them alive is not worth the 50dps they are gonna add. There are really only a couple of fights that we do that pets are not to be used - and the rest of the time it's a matter of the pet classes knowing that using a pet that will die in 40-60 seconds is not worth the trouble.
<br />

<br />
So, I disagree that pet classes are broken.  Pets can cause a problem on a couple of raids - if improperly used/positioned, but mainly dont have the durability to survive PoP fights, not to mention how high they get you on the agro list. Neither of those makes me broken. Unless you are fighting in PoEB which I have not seen, I just can't agree with you on this point.
<br />

<br />
It is my belief that pets DO push a little more than pcs do, but 20X is like, so not even close.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87433" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Ghoat!</a>
