				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I completely agree with the original poster. Pet push is a <span style="font-weight: bold">HUGE</span> problem for raids <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />. 
<br />

<br />
It's not so bad when you have just 1 pet, but once you have like 4 or more pets on something, the effects seem to multiply and the mob will be thrown around like a ragdoll. I remember that Agnarr script, where there was just MT and the mage/beastlord pets on the mob while the rest was using archery, the poor mob was pushed around nearly at run speed -- poor tank. Whoever said pet generated push is even close to player push, sorry, that's simply not true to put it mildly. You can have a full raid force, 40+ melees on a mob, and it would not be moved noticeably at all. Put a couple of pets on it and the mob is at the wall in seconds. 
<br />

<br />
A toggle for pet push, /pet bash on|off or somesuch if it's just bash that causes the push, would help beastlords much more than MGB. Or rather, just remove all pet push altogether, with Storm and Wind it would not be missed even against spellcasting mobs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
