				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet push isn't even comparable to melee player push, unless we're maybe talking shield-using knights that are chain bashing. Sorry, I haven't made any tests about whether pet bashing generates similar push as player bashing does, since noone hardly ever uses shields and bashes. Either way, pet push is <span style="font-weight: bold">very very real</span>. You'd surely witness it if you'd take a few beastlord pets to a raid in some dungeon, like SSeru - the mobs will simply be smacked through the walls. 
<br />

<br />
Sure, you can blame the masters for not balancing the push from all directions. Except there are very few occasions on raids where you have the chance to position the pet precisely where you want it while somehow coordinating the placement with 10 other pet class members on the raid. Usually the pets simply won't path to where you want them to push from, that is, between the mob and the wall. That means you must simply back the pet off. Which is the same as not using a pet at all. Which is a serious problem, since beastlords without pets are significantly crippled.
<br />

<br />
PS: I've no idea about elemental planes, my guild hasn't gotten as far yet - maybe there's enough room in those places to position the pets as saw fit, dunno - but the problem is extremely obvious in VT, especially Seru and lower planes/other non-permarooted bosses. We also have 4 beastlords in the guild, perhaps that's more than you've used to see?</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Rastik on Wed Apr 09, 2003 8:01 pm, edited 1 time in total</span></td>
