You are right.  My example of an AE mob was a bad one for the reasoning you outlined.  They die on the first few rounds of a heavy damage AE'er, once they are within melee range.  Granted I have not encountered the entire fourth tier named yet, but so far, it seems around 50/50 on named mobs that a pet could live through the fight without serous healing.  Mobs that I know of that we could use pets would be like Hydrotha, some of the phoenixs and general in PoF, most of the named in PoA, RZ, fennin script, coirnav script and just about all content that leads to these named.  PoA avatars would be a good example of pets pushing mobs out of melee range or into hollow walls.  In addition, we have had horrid problems with pets and Tallon Zek that spawns in the hallway on the Rallos Zek script.
<br />

<br />
Kaatt:
<br />
Come back after you have killed something harder than Terris Thull.  Until then, if I where you, I would keep my mouth shut, because it make you look like a jackass.
<br />

<br />
All:
<br />
I may have been a little over zealous when I said 20 times a PC player (hehe), but it is defiantly more than a group PC can do on a raid.  I do not understand why and I do not pretend to know why it happens either, but take the example that you can get about 10-15 melee behind Rallos Zek the Warlord pushing him into the corner and he barely moves.  Then put one pet behind him and he has pined into the corner within 30 seconds.  To any of you that do not think this is a problem based on soloing or grouping, I invite you to reply once you have raided along the lines of Rallos Zek or harder and see this problem first hand.
<br />

<br />
I just want to use my pet on raids where he will not die instantly and raid leaders will not let us.  I do not know any guilds on prexus that allows pets on third to fourth tier content specifically because of the pushing issue and making it much harder to keep a mob still.<br />_________________<br /><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450587>Maujin Buu</a>: 65 Feral Lord - Prexus
