			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rastik, I'm surprised your guild hasn't worked out how the moderate pet push benefits raids rather than impedes.
<br />

<br />
Pet's attack from main tank side (front) while rogues and monks at rear while pallies sk's etc either attack from side or back to make correct balance. The pets do not take riposte damage and so perfect to push from front so the high dps classes can live up to their name at the rear.
<br />

<br />
When we don't use pets then usually the push goes haywire as tanks don't like getting riposted for 2-3k per hit... especially dual wielding melee as they tend to die.
<br />

<br />
Even when I am soloing I prefer the pet to push so I am not chasing mobs all over the dungeon. You would never be able to keep your pet at the mob's back if it didn't push back.
<br />

<br />
Shere Khaan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
